text: Bosselshausen is a commune. It is in Grand Est in the Bas-Rhin department in northeast France. Between 1974 and 2007 Kirrwiller-Bosselshausen was a only commune. In January 2007, the communes Bosselshausen and Kirrwiller were separated.Arrêté du 29 décembre 2006 portant modification aux circonscriptions administratives territoriales (création de communes) == References == Category:Communes in Bas-Rhin
